Definition: `sure' is sometimes used informally for `surely')
Example: the results are surely encouraging; she certainly is a hard worker; it's going to be a good day for sure; they are coming, for certain; they thought he had been killed sure enough; he'll win sure as shooting; they sure smell good; sure he'll come
Synonyms: adj, all, sure, certainly, certain, for_sure, for_certain, sure_enough, sure_as_shooting, noun, communication, colloquialism, u, definitely, or, positively, is, sometimes, used, informally, for, the, results, are, encouraging, she, a, hard, worker, it, s, going, to, be, good, day, they, coming, thought, he, had, been, killed, enough, ll, win, as, shooting, smell, come
Category: adv.all
